<title type="html"><![CDATA[Use of the in vblank flag.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5357&amp;p=48452#p48452"><![CDATA[
You can use it if missing frames isn't an issue, but I don't understand why you'd ditch the NMI. It's perfectly possible and not hard at all to do everything with NMIs instead.<br /><br />Maybe you have your NMI tailored for in-game logic? It shouldn't be hard to make it work with other "sections" (such as the title screen) of your program as well.<br /><br />BTW, it's misleading to call it "the in vblank flag", because it's cleared as soon as you read it, it does not stay set during all of Vblank. Although it would be really helpful if it did!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue Jun 30, 2009 4:53 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
